adulterate
	v. render (something) poorer in quality by adding another substance, typically an inferior one
spurious
	adj. not being what it purports to be; false or fake
deftness
	adj. skillful performance or ability without difficulty
deride
	v. express contempt for; ridicule
banal
	adj. bland
glib
	adj. (of words or the person speaking them) fluent and voluble but insincere and shallow
olfactory
	adj. relating to smell
homily
	a religious discourse that is intended for primarily for spiritual edification rather than doctrinal instruction
edification
	n. the instruction or improvement of a person morally or intellectually
coda
	n. the concluding passage of a piece or movement